them. You could

45:14.712 --> 45:17.148 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have fun fixing them. There was
nowhere better.

45:17.181 --> 45:22.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It's the natural
world, though,
the world of plant life, that
ultimately grabbed

45:22.520 --> 45:22.987 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you.

45:23.020 --> 45:23.521 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
HOPE JAHREN: Yes.

45:23.554 --> 45:25.289 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Why?

45:25.323 --> 45:27.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HOPE JAHREN: Oh, it's the
biggest question
there is. What does it mean to
be alive on

45:27.658 --> 45:29.427 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the planet?

45:29.460 --> 45:33.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And answering that for you and
me is one thing,
